            <p><strong>Revenue model:</strong> Tiered subscriptions — Free (offline journal, zero hosting cost), $2/mo (cloud sync + MCP access), $5/mo (cloud transcription + cleanup), $10/mo (AI reflections, vector search, synthesis). Because Parachute complements rather than competes with AI subscriptions, the addressable market is every AI user — over 100 million people and growing rapidly — plus everyone who wants a great journaling app regardless of AI usage.</p>
            <p><strong>Why COGS are low:</strong> Transcription and embeddings cost a fraction of heavy AI inference. We're not running full agentic workloads — we're storing and serving structured data via MCP. As model costs continue to decline, margins improve further.</p>
            <p><strong>Path to profitability:</strong> Year two approaches breakeven (~$480K ARR vs ~$500K total opex). Year three is clearly profitable (~$3M ARR vs ~$1.2M total opex). These projections are conservative given the scale of the addressable market.</p>
            <p><strong>Funding to date:</strong> $0. The entire product has been built by the founder with no outside funding.</p>
        </div>
